channel.description: Is there anyway to make "null" items appear as the regular item? Or cant this be done? Thanks

item.title: Null Items
item.dc:creator: @pwnedurmom pwnedurmom
item.description:
@pwnedurmom wrote:

Patrickftw:

Get a model…Gzip it…Create the ints(Zoom, model IDs, rotation, sleeves, female, male), Which is difficult because they could be from 1-1000 in numbers. And they’re all different.

i don’t think he understands what you mean lawl…
tbh i wouldn’t have a clue about it if i hadn’t of made my own client…

nulls are just an object that hasn’t been put into your client yet…
if you downloaded a client and used to play silabsoft 70% of the time the skillcape ids are 9001-9100 (it was a guess)
so if you tryed to spawn a skillcape with like ::pickup 14235 2(huntercapeT on silab) it would be a null item on your client…
